It’s like I won the lottery 🎰 wine tasting and dinner with Sissy on a kid free night 🍷 🍽️ and Mom life means forgetting to post the content until a whole week after 😂
I kiddd 😂😂 bc I’ve already worked out this morning 💪 it’s called having a toddler at home 🦖🏡⚽️

Its Sunday and I forget how much I can get done at home without Jordy running circles around me 😂 Spent the morning focusing on self care, some house chores and making my boys lunch 🥙 

Since hubby took Jordan to the kids museum for a special daddy/son date and plans dates like this often, I’ve been intentionally mindful with my time alone🤍 
 
So into this minimal look for a girls dinner or date night 🥂 And it’s perfect for our annual family dinner tonight to celebrate the three January birthdays (hubby, mom and brother-in-law) 

#momfashionblogger #womensclothes #springdress #mommyblog #naplesblogger #naplesflorida #minimaloutfit #springoutfits

Spending the weekend focused on being Jordy’s Mom. This is a reminder to myself and all other moms (juggling life like all star professional athletes) to let the laundry pile up, groceries run low, home stay a mess and let yourself enjoy the moment with a heart so full 💕 It’s so freaking easy to miss out on the little thing that we call life when dividing your attention among being a mom, wife, working professional, maintaining the household and taking care of your own needs. Jordy kept saying ‘my mommy’ and squeezing me tight on our lounge day at home yesterday 😍 These slow weekends full of giggles, snuggles and precious time together are just what the doctor ordered 🙏🏼 #momlifeisthebestlife #mommyblog #naplesblogger #toddlermomlife #naplesflorida
